name: language_sql_data_line_comment_marker
description: |
  Two hyphens can begin an SQL line comment after unsafe interpolation, hiding
  closing syntax or later predicates. As a parameter value they must remain two
  ordinary characters.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
tags:
  - "language"
  - "sql"
  - "sql-data"
  - "string"
  - "line-comment"
  - "escaping"
  - "injection-canary"
---
--
